  "title": "Project/Site Engineer, Construction (Rotating Shift)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Support and oversee urgent construction activities and progress, plan, implement and monitor work (Industrial/Institutional Project, Rotating Shift Pattern)</li>\n  <li>Schedule in accordance to the master and detailed work program</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants (QPS) for technical issues and coordinate the site activities with subcontractors</li>\n  <li>Handle of technical and engineering problems</li>\n  <li>Provide guidance to supervisors in relation to construction works, ensure progress according to schedule</li>\n  <li>Maintain quality standards, carry out site inspections and resolve technical issues on time</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree in Civil, Engineering or relevant discipline</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2-4 years of relevant experience on Manufacturing/Industrial, Institutional or Building Projects</li>\n  <li>Comfortable to be on rotating shift pattern (Day-Night rotate)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If this opportunity aligns with your skills and experience, please submit your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p>\n<p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p>\n<p>bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
